Oil, Gas and Consumable Fuels

Company Overview of Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the refining and marketing of petroleum products in Thailand and internationally. It operates through Refinery, Marketing, Electricity, Biofuel, and Exploration and Production of Petroleum segments. The company also produces and distributes biodiesel, as well as electricity from solar cells. In addition, it offers various fuel products, and lubricants for automotive and industrial products; Bangchak personal cards that provides discounts to people who make payments at its service stations using the cards; and Bangchak corporate cards to business owners/entrepreneurs for convenience and financial flexibili...
Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the refining and marketing of petroleum products in Thailand and internationally. It operates through Refinery, Marketing, Electricity, Biofuel, and Exploration and Production of Petroleum segments. The company also produces and distributes biodiesel, as well as electricity from solar cells. In addition, it offers various fuel products, and lubricants for automotive and industrial products; Bangchak personal cards that provides discounts to people who make payments at its service stations using the cards; and Bangchak corporate cards to business owners/entrepreneurs for convenience and financial flexibility. Further, the company provides auto-care, oil-replacement, and car-washing and waxing services under Green Auto Service, Green Serve, Green Wash, and Green Wash Express names; operates retail stores; and operates coffee shops at its service stations under the Inthanin brand. Additionally, it engages in the trading of petroleum commodities; and exploration and production of petroleum. Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited markets its oil products to various sectors, including transportation, aviation, shipping, construction, industrial, and agriculture sectors; and sells its oil products through oil traders. The company was formerly known as The Bangchak Petroleum Public Company Limited and changed its name to Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited in April 2017. Bangchak Corporation Public Company Limited is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand.
Detailed Description


